The paper deals with the problem of secret key generation through a relay, which involves information theory, cryptography, and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication and information processing. The paper also involves security and privacy, which suggests the category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of a relay and communication links suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves system-level design and optimization, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the use of coding techniques suggests the category cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
